<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFD6AF2FC98E9A06FD5A940D" blockId="3.[151,759,343,370]" box="[151,759,343,370]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">
<heading id="D0859D37FFD6AF2FC98E9A06FD5A940D" bold="true" box="[151,759,343,370]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="3" pageNumber="566" reason="1">
<taxonomicName id="4C7251D8FFD6AF2FC98E9A06FD5A940D" authority="Engel &amp; Grimaldi, 2008" authorityName="Engel &amp; Grimaldi" authorityYear="2008" box="[151,759,343,370]" class="Insecta" family="Prostomidae" genus="Vetuprostomis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="566" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="consimilis">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD6AF2FC98E9A06FD5A940D" bold="true" box="[151,759,343,370]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD6AF2FC98E9A06FE69940D" bold="true" box="[151,452,343,370]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">Vetuprostomis consimilis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE357AAFFD6AF2FC8D29A06FD5A940D" author="Engel, M. S. &amp; Grimaldi, D. A." box="[459,759,344,370]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566" pagination="215 - 218" refId="ref5071" refString="Engel, M. S. &amp; Grimaldi, D. A. (2008) A jugular-horned beetle in Cretaceous amber from Myanmar (Coleoptera: Prostomidae). Alavesia, 2, 215 - 218." type="journal article" year="2008">Engel &amp; Grimaldi, 2008</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36879D0FFD6AF2FC98E9AFEFEF997ED" pageId="3" pageNumber="566" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFD6AF2FC98E9AFEFEF997ED" blockId="3.[151,1437,416,658]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD6AF2FC98E9AFEFEA694C5" bold="true" box="[151,267,416,442]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">Remarks.</emphasis>
The original description and illustrations of this species by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE357AAFFD6AF2FCAA89AFEFB6294C5" author="Engel, M. S. &amp; Grimaldi, D. A." box="[945,1231,416,442]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566" pagination="215 - 218" refId="ref5071" refString="Engel, M. S. &amp; Grimaldi, D. A. (2008) A jugular-horned beetle in Cretaceous amber from Myanmar (Coleoptera: Prostomidae). Alavesia, 2, 215 - 218." type="journal article" year="2008">Engel &amp; Grimaldi (2008)</bibRefCitation>
are not sufficient, which makes it difficult to provide a detailed comparison between 
<taxonomicName id="4C7251D8FFD6AF2FCA9D9A9BFBBF94A1" authorityName="Engel &amp; Grimaldi" authorityYear="2008" box="[900,1042,452,478]" class="Insecta" family="Prostomidae" genus="Vetuprostomis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="566" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="consimilis">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD6AF2FCA9D9A9BFBBF94A1" box="[900,1042,452,478]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">V. consimilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the two new species described here. In one of their line drawings (fig. 2C in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE357AAFFD6AF2FCB979AB6FC34977D" author="Engel, M. S. &amp; Grimaldi, D. A." box="[654,921,488,514]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566" pagination="215 - 218" refId="ref5071" refString="Engel, M. S. &amp; Grimaldi, D. A. (2008) A jugular-horned beetle in Cretaceous amber from Myanmar (Coleoptera: Prostomidae). Alavesia, 2, 215 - 218." type="journal article" year="2008">Engel &amp; Grimaldi 2008</bibRefCitation>
), the penultimate palpomere of both maxillary palps seems to be distinctly shortened, which if true, could serve as a distinctive character separating 
<taxonomicName id="4C7251D8FFD6AF2FCC169953FA309759" authorityName="Engel &amp; Grimaldi" authorityYear="2008" box="[1295,1437,524,550]" class="Insecta" family="Prostomidae" genus="Vetuprostomis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="566" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="consimilis">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD6AF2FCC169953FA309759" box="[1295,1437,524,550]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">V. consimilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7251D8FFD6AF2FC9CA996FFEF49735" authorityName="Li &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[211,345,560,586]" class="Insecta" family="Prostomidae" genus="Vetuprostomis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="566" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angularis">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD6AF2FC9CA996FFEF49735" box="[211,345,560,586]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">V. angularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7251D8FFD6AF2FC894996FFE749735" authorityName="Li &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[397,473,561,586]" class="Insecta" family="Prostomidae" genus="Vetuprostomis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="566" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gaoi">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD6AF2FC894996FFE749735" box="[397,473,561,586]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="566">V. gaoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, in another line drawing (fig. 2A in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE357AAFFD6AF2FCACC996EFB739735" author="Engel, M. S. &amp; Grimaldi, D. A." box="[981,1246,560,586]" pageId="3" pageNumber="566" pagination="215 - 218" refId="ref5071" refString="Engel, M. S. &amp; Grimaldi, D. A. (2008) A jugular-horned beetle in Cretaceous amber from Myanmar (Coleoptera: Prostomidae). Alavesia, 2, 215 - 218." type="journal article" year="2008">Engel &amp; Grimaldi 2008</bibRefCitation>
), the penultimate palpomere of left maxillary palp appears to have a longer length. Thus, the effectiveness of this character should be treated carefully.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
